<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-02-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-02-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="725" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2672a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-02-14T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 14,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>6. The Department desires to be kept promptly and fully informed
                            regarding political conditions in Santo Domingo. Department has not yet
                            been informed of promulgation of electoral law, or if it has not yet
                            been promulgated, as to the reasons for its delay. Please report in
                            detail regarding this and all other political matters.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>